- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with analyzing large data streams and discusses issues related to continuously augmented data sets. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper discusses segmentation of customers, which can be seen as a form of multi-agent systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the proposed method to marketing data, which can be seen as a form of computational science. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the EM algorithm, which is a fundamental concept in information theory.
